Mouse RNA-interacting proteins

This database provides curated information on proteins that are involved in RNA processing and contain RNA-binding domain(s) in mouse. Currently 1,369 RNA processing-related proteins and RNA-binding proteins are listed.

This information was manually curated from several databases:

(Domain) RNA binding protein database (RBPDB, v1.3 release 28.09.2012); ATtRACT (A daTabase of RNA binding proteins and AssoCiated moTifs, Ver 0.99β); InterPro domain database; UniProt mouse proteins (reviewed, 2018) with domains. (Function) UniProt mouse proteins (reviewed, 2018) with Gene Ontology (GO) information; KEGG pathway related to RNA processing; RNA modification database from the RNA institute at Albany; Reactome database ("RNA metabolism"-related proteins). (Transcript abundance in mouse renal tubules) RNA-Seq data provides abundance of transcripts (rank of each transcript in all 13,526 transcripts) expressed in mouse whole kidney samples and microdissected mouse renal tubules. Please see details of RNS-Seq data in the databse for "RNA-seq Analysis of Mouse Whole Kidney and Microdissected Mouse Renal Tubules". S2, middle segment of proximal tubule; cTAL, cortical thick ascending limb of the loop of Henle; CCD, cortical collecting duct.

This database was created by Hyun Jun Jung and Mark A. Knepper in the Epithelial Systems Biology Laboratory at the National Heart, Lung and Blood Institute as part of its Kidney Systems Biology Project. Please contact Mark Knepper (Epithelial Systems Biology Laboratory, NHLBI) at knep@helix.nih.gov or go to Epithelial Systems Biology Laboratory for further information.
